<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1265,1974]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1877,1902]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Mesial process of G1 large, subquadrate; mesial side of apical plate smooth, devoid of spines; subapical bulge noticeable in sternal view; subapical bulge and crest of sternal lobe both covered by abundant spinules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
